                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/633.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Clark says revenues November insufficient for payment cost of collection and
                    interest due November 30. New York bankers refuse loan. Can anything be done to
                    prevent default?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buckner</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
